The paper proposes a new algorithm for sparse signal recovery in the context of multiple-measurement vectors (MMV) problem. This problem is related to compressed sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm is based on iterative sparse representation using zero-point attracting projection (ZAP), which involves optimization techniques that are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves projection to satisfy under-determined equations, which is a signal processing technique (cs.SP). The paper mentions the use of a variable step size scheme to improve convergence and accuracy, which is a numerical analysis technique (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to the Modulated Wideband Converter, which is a system identification problem and falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
